org.gradoop.temporal.model.api.functions

Interface TemporalPredicate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    All, AsOf, Between, ContainedIn, CreatedIn, DeletedIn, FromTo, Overlaps, Precedes, Succeeds, ValidDuring
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface TemporalPredicate
extends Serializable
    A predicate that selects certain time-stamps or time-intervals.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean test(long from, long to)
      Evaluates this predicate for a certain time-stamp or -interval.

    • Method Detail

      • test

        boolean test(long from,
             long to)
        Evaluates this predicate for a certain time-stamp or -interval. If this predicate only operates on time-stamps, the second argument will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        from - The start of the time-interval. (Or the time-stamp.)
        to - The end of the time-interval. (Ignored, if this predicate only operates on time-stamps.)
        Returns:
        true, if the time-interval /-stamp matches this predicate.
